'''Snot''' was a simple game that was easy to learn. The [[Gamorrean/Legends|Gamorrean]] guard [[Gartogg/Legends|Gartogg]], due to a lack of intellect, was unable to learn how to play the game<ref name="GOAT">{{StoryCite|story=Goatgrass: The Tale of Ree-Yees|book=Tales from Jabba's Palace}}</ref> by [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]]. That [[Standard year/Legends|year]],<ref name="TERC">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' dates the events of "[[Goatgrass: The Tale of Ree-Yees]]," including [[Ree-Yees/Legends|Ree-Yees]]' thoughts on [[Gartogg/Legends|Gartogg]], to [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]].</ref> the [[Gran/Legends|Gran]] [[Ree-Yees/Legends|Ree-Yees]] knew this and took advantage of the Gamorrean's shortcoming to draw potential attention away from himself and the [[Death/Legends|death]] of the [[Human/Legends|Human]] scullion [[Phlegmin]].<ref name="GOAT" />

==Behind the scenes==
Snot was first mentioned in [[Deborah J. Ross]]'s short story "[[Goatgrass: The Tale of Ree-Yees]]," published in the anthology book ''[[Tales from Jabba's Palace]]'' in [[1995]].<ref name="GOAT" /> In real life, snot is a uncouth term for [[Wikipedia:Nasal mucosa|nasal mucus]].<ref name="Dict">{{WebCite|url=https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/snot|text=Snot Definition & Meaning|work=[[Wikipedia:Merriam-Webster|Merriam-Webster]]|archivedate=20211012190232}}</ref>

